Progressive slashing (per operator, per adjudicated bad round):
10% → 25% → 50% → 100% (ban), with violation decay over time already in code.

Expected attacker cost vs gain (simple bound):

Expected penalty per bad round across t colluders:


E[Penalty$] ≥ p_det × t × (current B_op$) × (slash_bps / 10,000)

For any plan of n rounds, require:


∑ E[Penalty$]_round ≥ SF × MDP$

> With p_det = 0.7 and the 10→25→50→100% curve, break-even needs unrealistically high success & luck—your “>80%” observation stands; this curve keeps it that way.




